1 (2) Nothing in [sections 1 through 9] prohibits or limits the types of exclusions pet insurers may use
2 in their policies or require pet insurers to have any of the limitations or exclusions defined below.
3 (3) As used in [sections 1 through 9], the following definitions apply:
4 (a) "Chronic condition" means a condition that can be treated or managed, but not cured.
5 (b) "Congenital anomaly or disorder" means a condition that is present from birth, whether
6 inherited or caused by the environment, which may cause or contribute to illness or disease.
7 (c) "Hereditary disorder" means an abnormality that is genetically transmitted from parent to
8 offspring and may cause illness or disease.
9 (d) "Orthopedic" refers to conditions affecting the bones, skeletal muscle, cartilage, tendons,
10 ligaments, and joints. It includes but is not limited to elbow dysplasia, hip dysplasia, intervertebral disc
11 degeneration, patellar luxation, and ruptured cranial cruciate ligaments. It does not include cancers or
12 metabolic, hemopoietic, or autoimmune diseases.
13
14 (e) "Pet" means any domesticated animal normally maintained in or near the household of its
15 owner. It does not include livestock as defined in 81-8-213 kept for any commercial purpose.
16 (f) "Pet insurance" means a property insurance policy that provides coverage for accidents and
17 illnesses of pets.
18 (g) (i) "Preexisting condition" means any condition for which any of the following are true prior to
19 the effective date of a pet insurance policy or during any waiting period:
20 (A) a veterinarian provided medical advice;
21 (B) the pet received previous treatment; or
22 (C) based on information from verifiable sources, the pet had signs or symptoms directly related to
23 the condition for which a claim is being made.
24 (ii) A condition for which coverage is afforded on a policy cannot be considered a preexisting
25 condition on any renewal of the policy.
26 (h) "Renewal" means to issue and deliver at the end of an insurance policy period a policy that
27 supersedes a policy previously issued and delivered by the same pet insurer or affiliated pet insurer and that
28 provides types and limits of coverage substantially similar to those contained in the policy being superseded.
