11 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Sales practices for wellness programs. (1) A pet insurer and producer
12 selling pet insurance may not:
13 (a) market a wellness program as pet insurance; or
14 (b) market a wellness program during the sale, solicitation, or negotiation of pet insurance.
15 (2) If a wellness program is sold by a pet insurer and producer:
16 (a) the purchase of the wellness program may not be a requirement to the purchase of pet
17 insurance;
18 (b) the costs of the wellness program must be separate and identifiable from any pet insurance
19 policy;
20 (c) the terms and conditions for the wellness program must be separate from any pet insurance
21 policy;
22 (d) the products or coverages available through the wellness program may not duplicate products
23 or coverages available through the pet insurance policy;
24 (e) the advertising of the wellness program may not be misleading and must be in accordance with
25 this subsection (2); and
26 (f) the pet insurer and producer shall clearly disclose the following to consumers, printed in at
27 least 12-point boldface type:
28 (i) that wellness programs are not insurance;
